The paper deals with the identification of mobile app traffic, which falls under the category of network security and network monitoring. Therefore, cs.NI (Network and Distributed Systems) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models for classification, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper deals with mobile multimedia traffic, which could make cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a CNN+LSTM model, which is a type of deep learning architecture, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category as well.
